## **0. HTML Basics**

**<html>** â€“ root element (contains all of HTML)

**HTML element** â€“ opening tag + content + closing tag

**<nav>** â€“ container for navigation links  
Example:
```html
<nav>
    <a href="#home">Home</a>
    <a href="#about">About</a>
    <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
</nav>
```

**<span>** â€“ styling hook, inline, no semantic meaning  
Example:
```html
<p>This is <span style="color:red;">important</span> text.</p>
```

## **1. Forms in HTML**

Forms allow users to **submit data** (like name, email, or comments).

**Basic Syntax:**

```html
<form>

    <!-- Name -->
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required><br><br>

    <!-- Gender (Radio Buttons) Same name + radio button = only one choice-->
    <p>Gender:</p>
    <label>
        <input type="radio" name="gender" value="male" > Male
    </label>
    <label>
        <input type="radio" name="gender" value="female"> Female
    </label><br><br>

    <!-- Skills (Checkboxes) -->
    <p>Skills:</p>
    <label>
        <input type="checkbox" name="skills" value="html"> HTML
    </label>
    <label>
        <input type="checkbox" name="skills" value="css"> CSS
    </label>
    <label>
        <input type="checkbox" name="skills" value="javascript"> JavaScript
    </label><br><br>

    <!-- Dropdown Menu -->
    <label for="course">Select Course:</label>
    <select id="course" name="course" required>
        <option value="" disabled selected>Select</option>
        <option value="frontend">Frontend</option>
        <option value="backend">Backend</option>
        <option value="fullstack">Full Stack</option>
    </select><br><br>

    <!-- Comment -->
    <label for="comment">Comment:</label><br>
    <textarea id="comment" name="comment" rows="4" cols="40"></textarea><br><br>

    <!-- Submit Button -->
    <button type="submit">Submit</button>

</form>

```

**Key Points:**

* `<form>`: wraps the entire form.
* `action`: URL where form data is sent.
* `method`: `post` (data hidden) or `get` (data visible in URL).
* `<label>`: descriptive text for input (good for accessibility).
* `<input>`: text box, email, password, radio, checkbox, etc.
* `<textarea>`: multi-line text input.
* `<button type="submit">`: submits the form.
* `required `: to make a field mandatory.



âœ… **Common Mistakes:**

* Forgetting `type` or `name` in `<input>`
* Using `<p>` instead of `<label>`
* Forgetting to close `<textarea>`

---

## **2. Image Syntax**

Images are displayed using the `<img>` tag.

**Syntax:**

```html
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Description of the image" width="300" height="200">
```

**Key Points:**

* `<img>` is a **void element** â†’ no closing tag needed.
* `src`: path or URL of the image.
* `alt`: alternative text (for accessibility and if image fails to load).
* `width` and `height`: optional size attributes (can also use CSS).
---

## **3. Link Syntax**

Links allow users to **navigate to other pages or websites**.

**Syntax:**

```html
<a href="https://www.example.com" target="_blank">Click Here</a>
```

**Key Points:**

* `<a>` = anchor tag
* `href`: URL to link to
* `target="_blank"`: opens link in new tab
* Link text goes **between `<a>` and `</a>`**
---

## **4. Tables**

Tables organize **data in rows and columns**.

**Syntax:**

```html
<table border="1">
    <tr>
        <th>Header 1</th>
        <th>Header 2</th>
        <th>Header 3</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Row 1, Col 1</td>
        <td>Row 1, Col 2</td>
        <td>Row 1, Col 3</td>
    </tr>
    
</table>
```

**Key Points:**

* `<th>` = table header (bold, centered by default)
* `<td>` = table data (normal cell)
* `border="1"` = adds border around table (can also use CSS for styling)

ðŸ’¡ **Quick Cheat Sheet:**

| Feature | Tag/Attribute                                 | Example                                  |
| ------- | --------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| Form    | `<form>`, `<input>`, `<textarea>`, `<button>` | `<input type="text" name="name">`        |
| Image   | `<img src="" alt="">`                         | `<img src="image.jpg" alt="A baboon">`   |
| Link    | `<a href="">`                                 | `<a href="https://example.com">Link</a>` |
| Table   | `<table>`, `<tr>`, `<th>`, `<td>`, `border`   | `<th>Header</th>` `<td>Data</td>`        |


## Other Stuff I Don't Know

### HTML Elements & Attributes â€“ Quick Guide

**1. Void elements (no closing tag):** `<img>`, `<br>`, `<hr>`

**2. Common Attributes**  
Attributes give extra information about an element.

| Attribute | Use | Example |
|-----------|-----|---------|
| `id` | Unique element | `<p id="intro">` |
| `class` | Group elements | `<div class="card">` |
| `href` | Link URL | `<a href="page.html">` |
| `src` | Image/video file | `<img src="pic.jpg">` |
| `alt` | Image description | `<img alt="A cat">` |
| `name` | Forms / radio buttons | `<input type="radio" name="gender">` |
| `target` | Where link opens | `<a target="_blank">` |

**3. ID vs Class**

| Feature | ID | Class |
|---------|----|-------|
| Uniqueness | Must be unique | Can repeat |
| CSS selector | `#id` | `.class` |
